In today's session I learnt types of css and diffrent methods to add css
Three ar etree methods 
1)Inline-Concentrating on only one elment in Html file
Exanple:
<html style="color:red;"</html>
2)Internal-Concentrating only one a one webpage.
Example:
<html lang="en">

<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Internal</title>
</head>
<style>
  h1{
    color:red;
  }
</style>

<body>
<h1>Style Me in Red!</h1>
</body>

</html>

3)External-Used in overall website using external style.css file
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>External</title>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Style Me in Green</h1>
   <link rel="stylesheet" href="./style.css"
</body>
</html>
